summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 12357, entitled "An Ordinance regulating the use of streets, avenues and alleys in the City of Seattle by horses and vehicles, and regulating the speed of horses and beasts of burden thereon on certain streets, avenues and alleys, and providing a penalty for any violation thereof, and repealing all ordinances and parts of ordinances in conflict herewith," approved May 3, 1905.
